Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Translation Function
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level pipeline driver: parse Markdown source into AST, then translate AST
to HIR. On any failure (null source, allocation failure, parse failure, or
has_error set during translation) frees all created context resources and
returns 0; otherwise returns the HIR document root. The translation_context
parameter is currently unused but reserved for the broader Translation system
to forward diagnostics upstream.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
The Markdown AST is consumed transiently — parse_markdown allocates the AST
nodes and the HIR translator only reads them, but the AST is intentionally
not freed here (HIR strings share lifetime via deep-copy in the parser).
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_markdown_to_hir" takes source_code as Integer, translation_context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate Markdown source code to Runa HIR

    If source_code is equal to 0:
        Note: Report error to Translation context (if available)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create translation context
    Let context be proc create_translation_context

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse Markdown
    Let md_ast be proc parse_markdown from Parser with source_code

    If md_ast is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_translation_context with context
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Translate to HIR
    Let hir_root be proc translate_markdown_node_to_hir with context, md_ast

    Note: Check for translation errors
    Let has_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8

    If has_error is equal to 1:
        proc destroy_translation_context with context
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Cleanup
    proc destroy_translation_context with context

    Return hir_root
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Single-Argument Source Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public single-arg facade invoked by the translation dispatcher's
LANG_MARKDOWN arm. translate_markdown_to_hir already takes source
plus a reserved translation_context pointer (unused at present, see
docstring); this wrapper forwards with translation_context=0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Direct forward to translate_markdown_to_hir(source_code, 0). Returns 0
on parse or translation failure (propagated from the underlying call).
@End Implementation

Process called "markdown_to_hir_from_source" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc translate_markdown_to_hir with source_code, 0
End Process

Note: End of Markdown to HIR Translator
